MP Version 1.07 program, the entire inventory is assumed to release and ignite, resulting in a vapor cloud explosion that reaches the 1 psi overpressure point at 0.4 miles. Since the facility is located in an unpopulated area the WCS will not affect offsite endpoints or public receptors. A consideration of the 0.4 mile radius has been incorporated into our notification and emergency response planning.



Atlas's management is committed to doing the following:



-Preventing accidents;

-Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;

-Participating in community emergency preparedness;

-Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Atlas operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and

-Being a good corporate citizen of Woods County.



With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the natural gas treatment and liquids recovery process. Most importantly, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe operation for our employees, our visitors, and our community.
